00:01:57.820 --> 00:01:59.240
Despite these differences,

00:01:59.240 --> 00:02:03.660
both Pharisees and Sadducees were
represented in the Great Sanhedrin,

00:02:03.660 --> 00:02:08.720
the Jewish High Court, where among other
things civil and religious laws were interpreted.

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:13.330
Sadducees held various political
social and religious roles,

00:02:13.330 --> 00:02:17.610
including maintaining the temple. Now
their high social status

00:02:17.610 --> 00:02:21.390
was reinforced by their priestly responsibilities

00:02:21.390 --> 00:02:26.990
as mandated in the Torah. Pharisees on
the other hand...  

00:02:28.549 --> 00:02:31.819
...Pharisees had the backing and
goodwill of

00:02:31.819 --> 00:02:36.359
the common people in contrast to the more elite Sadducees.

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:40.620
They were in a sense
middle-class Jews who many considered

00:02:40.629 --> 00:02:42.189
the spiritual fathers of modern

00:02:42.189 --> 00:02:47.010
Judaism. They believe for example in the
resurrection of the dead,

00:02:47.010 --> 00:02:51.829
existence of an afterlife, and that God punish the wicked and rewarded the righteous

00:02:52.359 --> 00:02:56.039
in the world to come,    while Sadducees...

00:02:57.580 --> 00:03:01.079
Sadducees rejected any notions of

00:03:01.079 --> 00:03:05.319
afterlife. Now, on these points then Jesus
and the Pharisees would have been in agreement.

00:03:05.329 --> 00:03:09.340
